1
00:00:15,530 --> 00:00:16,970
Everybody here is talking, you know?

2
00:00:17,930 --> 00:00:19,700
About you bringing a knife to the audition.

3
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:22,700
To both of P'Kajorn's superstars.

4
00:00:24,130 --> 00:00:24,800
Bottoms up.

5
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:29,700
Calling every photographer to an event?

6
00:00:30,770 --> 00:00:32,070
So, what exactly do you want?

7
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,370
In this industry, who is the best photographer?

8
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:36,930
Hey, who are you guys?

9
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:39,800
I'm asking for real.

10
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,800
Do you believe in karma?

11
00:01:41,370 --> 00:01:43,970
How can you be so confident that you'll survive in this industry?

12
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,770
Remember what I told you?

13
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:32,530
That in this world, nothing comes for free.

14
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:39,970
Right now, you owe me another 50,000 because you asked me to scold your manager.

15
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,230
And 200,000 for the cigarettes.

16
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:45,930
The question is, are you ready to pay me back?

17
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:48,000
I have nothing but myself.

18
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:55,670
You came all the way here.

19
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,130
What were you expecting?

20
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:04,400
Did you ever imagine

21
00:03:05,930 --> 00:03:07,600
that I would suddenly make a move on you?

22
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:12,770
Putting what's mine inside you.

23
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:19,770
I've actually thought about that before.

24
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:24,730
But it would be me putting what's mine inside your body.

25
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,500
And then moving it aggressively.

26
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:06,200
In here, there are five short films

27
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:07,770
25 minutes each.

28
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:09,370
Watch them all.

29
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,070
How was it?

30
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,400
What did you find out?

31
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,870
So, who exactly is that guy?

32
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,100
What's his name?

33
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:43,900
Where does he work?

34
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,000
What about his home?

35
00:05:45,130 --> 00:05:46,600
What's his background?

36
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,300
Calm down, sir.

37
00:05:50,170 --> 00:05:51,500
You're firing questions at me like this,

38
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,230
how can I answer them in time?

39
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,930
Then answer them one by one.

40
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,400
First, who is that guy?

41
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:13,070
I don't have much information on that kid.

42
00:06:13,170 --> 00:06:15,170
All I know is his name is Songbaht.

43
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:16,130
Huh?

44
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:18,370
What kind of person...

45
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,600
What kind of person is named Songbaht?

46
00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:23,570
And, and, and...

47
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,900
How did he know my Jay?

48
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,970
And why are they so close?

49
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:30,730
To the point that my Jay lets him into his private room.

50
00:06:31,770 --> 00:06:34,130
Even I am not allowed in there.

51
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:40,500
For this matter, I think you should ask Khun Jay yourself.

52
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:44,270
If I asked and he answered,

53
00:06:44,970 --> 00:06:46,800
why would I waste time having you investigate?

54
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:48,970
Useless.

55
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,130
Keep a close eye on him.

56
00:06:55,670 --> 00:06:57,230
If you see that...

57
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:59,400
that Songbaht guy

58
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,100
come here again

59
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:03,970
report to me immediately.

60
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:06,270
Yes, sir.

61
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,330
This won't do it.

62
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,770
Looks like I'll have to take matters into my own hands this time.

63
00:07:57,330 --> 00:07:58,070
How were they?

64
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:06,070
They were good.

65
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:08,700
If you had to choose,

66
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,700
which one would you pick?

67
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:13,230
Probably the first one.

68
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,330
And also the fourth one.

69
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:20,030
Those two

70
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,270
are directed by the same director.

71
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:23,830
His name is Karn.

72
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,500
You've got good instincts.

73
00:08:27,730 --> 00:08:30,270
I’m trying to scout and build up a new director.

74
00:08:32,830 --> 00:08:35,130
Because Dream Entertainment is going to invest in making its own films.

75
00:08:39,070 --> 00:08:40,570
What kind of business do you actually do?

76
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:43,200
I do many things.

77
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:45,670
Both at Dream,

78
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,870
and I'm also a shareholder in this club.

79
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:54,000
So what exactly is the reason that you called me here today?

80
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:58,370
I’m not here just to watch these movies, right?

81
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:01,830
Maybe you are.

82
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:07,170
I just wanted to use someone who has absolutely no vested interest here.

83
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,670
I know you used to work as an illegal debt collector.

84
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,230
I know that both your mother and brother are dead.

85
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:20,030
I know that after both of them are dead then you wanted to become a better person.

86
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,570
I hired a detective to look into you.

87
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,000
Now I know everything about you.

88
00:09:29,330 --> 00:09:30,970
I know you used to date Sunny.

89
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:34,270
Otherwise known as Bank Thanaphat.

90
00:09:35,370 --> 00:09:37,200
He stole your money and ran away.

91
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:08,300
And I don't know how you actually convinced Phakin,

92
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:11,400
so that guy agreed to take photos for you.

93
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,200
Still, you're pretty impressive.

94
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,600
The reason I called you here today

95
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,430
is because I have a gift for you.

96
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,270
Let me put it in.

97
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,030
If you come any closer,

98
00:10:32,130 --> 00:10:33,470
I could literally kill you.

99
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:36,830
Talking like that actually turns me on.

100
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:45,930
An audio clip of Sunny talking about you.

101
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:18,200
What are they talking about in there?

102
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:27,670
How did you manage to record this?

103
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,270
Why wouldn't I be able to?

104
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,900
Actors and artists come to hang out here all the time.

105
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:44,170
And they love to spill everything to the staff that they like.

106
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:55,930
Didn’t I tell you already?

107
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,130
I'm a shareholder of this club.

108
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,200
Now, what is the next step on your revenge agenda?

109
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:07,900
What do I need to do

110
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:12,100
to get a chance to be in the same circle as Director Arthur?

111
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:19,870
I want to be Dream's number one actor.

112
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,400
Finally,

113
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:28,130
you finally admit that you want Director Arthur as your backer.

114
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:41,900
Your homework.

115
00:12:43,730 --> 00:12:45,070
Finish reading these.

116
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:47,170
Then come summarize them for me tomorrow.

117
00:12:52,370 --> 00:12:54,700
I must find out who you really are.

118
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,000
Mr. Songbaht.

119
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:10,100
How can reading all these, will actually lead me to Director Arthur?

120
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:16,230
Director Arthur doesn't like incompetent people.

121
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:19,030
If you want to impress him,

122
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,370
you have to follow my orders unconditionally.

123
00:13:34,830 --> 00:13:36,400
Someone like Phakin

124
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:37,800
actually agreed to take photos for him.

125
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:41,170
Whatever.

126
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,200
Don't care who he is.

127
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:45,670
Get him out of my way quickly.

128
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:48,670
I'm sick of the trash like him hanging around Kajorn.

129
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,300
Don't let him succeed,

130
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:52,530
or have a place in this industry.

131
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:12,200
Hey, what are you eating, Bro?

132
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,700
How many times have I told you not to eat this kind of stuff?

133
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:18,270
Eating like this will make your hair fall out completely.

134
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:19,530
Stop eating.

135
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,000
I knew you'd be eating this kind of stuff.

136
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,030
But it's convenient.

137
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:26,530
And it's not expensive either.

138
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,300
I bought this for you.

139
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:33,130
Let's share it, so it'll taste better.

140
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:47,000
If you hold a grudge over that,

141
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,300
why didn't you just punch him when you met?

142
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:53,930
So it could all be over.

143
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:00,570
How are you doing? Are you ready for this evening?

144
00:15:02,730 --> 00:15:05,370
I'm totally ready for any stage play.

145
00:15:10,930 --> 00:15:11,730
Oh.

146
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:14,900
Have you seen this yet?

147
00:15:15,330 --> 00:15:16,500
I just saw it this morning.

148
00:15:17,830 --> 00:15:20,600
Phakin posted photos of Sun on his IG too.

149
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,030
Really?

150
00:15:25,570 --> 00:15:26,370
Wow!

151
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:28,100
On his personal IG account?

152
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,030
Yes.

153
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,500
Wow.

154
00:15:34,070 --> 00:15:35,270
He looks so handsome in this photo.

155
00:15:40,070 --> 00:15:42,470
Look at you, yawning from a mile away.

156
00:15:43,530 --> 00:15:45,330
You knew you had class today.

157
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:46,930
Why didn't you get enough sleep?

158
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,070
Look at this, Sun.

159
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:52,530
Mr. Phakin posted your photo on his IG.

160
00:15:52,730 --> 00:15:53,530
Here.

161
00:15:57,730 --> 00:15:59,000
Aren't you excited at all?

162
00:15:59,370 --> 00:16:01,770
He only posts photos of famous people.

163
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:06,030
Actually, this might just be backup shots.

164
00:16:06,430 --> 00:16:08,470
But Phakin seems to really like it.

165
00:16:10,170 --> 00:16:12,770
I feel like this picture gives off a vibe like...

166
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,230
Hmm, it's a bit complex.

167
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,670
What do you think, Sky?

168
00:16:19,930 --> 00:16:20,730
Hmm.

169
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:23,870
I think Khun Sun's eyes...

170
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:26,070
seem to convey some kind of intense emotion.

171
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:31,930
But it looks quite sad.

172
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,630
What a sharp interpretation.

173
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,030
Classic Sky.

174
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,630
Have you eaten anything yet, Sun?

175
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:55,570
I’m alright.

176
00:16:56,170 --> 00:16:56,970
Sun.

177
00:16:58,070 --> 00:17:00,030
This is your schedule for the whole week.

178
00:17:01,070 --> 00:17:05,170
You need to attend acting classes and go to action choreography training. Study hard, alright?

179
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:08,500
As for this, I want you to record every session

180
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,300
But wait,

181
00:17:15,170 --> 00:17:18,099
please don't lose it or break it.

182
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,930
This came out of my personal wallet.

183
00:17:27,569 --> 00:17:28,630
I don't know how to use it.

184
00:17:37,570 --> 00:17:39,130
Alright, come here, let me teach you.

185
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,200
It's not that hard.

186
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,870
This one isn't really hard to use at all.

187
00:17:49,170 --> 00:17:50,370
This side is the camera,

188
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:53,270
and this part is the power button.

189
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:57,170
When you want to record, you can just set it up like this.

190
00:17:57,470 --> 00:17:59,170
You'll be able to see your own face like this too.

191
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:01,600
And you can adjust the different modes with this button.

192
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:03,730
You can also set it up like this.

193
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:07,000
If you want to use the selfie stick,

194
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:08,230
you can do it this.

195
00:18:10,830 --> 00:18:11,800
Want to try?

196
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:18,970
Hey, Bro.

197
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,970
Why are you taking photos of the two of us?

198
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:31,130
Well, come to think of it, you two look good as a ship.

199
00:18:34,330 --> 00:18:36,770
Come on, nowadays you have to hype things up a bit.

200
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:40,930
Anyways.

201
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:45,600
Sun.

202
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:48,100
I have a stage play this evening.

203
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,070
Will you come to watch it?

204
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:53,400
Are you coming, P'Kajorn?

205
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:12,600
Dummy: What is the Children's Day official motto for this year?

206
00:19:13,870 --> 00:19:14,670
Of course.

207
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:17,770
What the hell?

208
00:19:19,370 --> 00:19:20,370
That’s dumb as hell.

209
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:41,570
Hi, you must be the new kid.

210
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:43,730
I'm Two-O.

211
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:46,100
Hey.

212
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:49,830
I'm Off.

213
00:19:50,530 --> 00:19:51,870
I just started classes not long ago.

214
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,100
Nice to meet you.

215
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:56,000
Likewise.

216
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:25,030
I heard you’re just a trainee.

217
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,430
You look like you don’t have any money at all,

218
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,730
so you probably won't last even a month.

219
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:36,130
I don't really know why you came to drag the company down.

220
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:41,930
Ugh, this is so upsetting.

221
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:46,230
It seems like everyone wants to be an actor these days.

222
00:20:49,570 --> 00:20:51,670
Looks like you've chosen such a rough path.

223
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:56,600
But welcome.

224
00:20:58,970 --> 00:20:59,770
I'm Wave.

225
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,170
Hello, everyone.

226
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:08,500
How is everyone doing?

227
00:21:09,730 --> 00:21:10,970
You guys are doing well, right?

228
00:21:13,930 --> 00:21:16,500
Okay, before we begin today,

229
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:19,970
I have some good news to share.

230
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,170
And it is,

231
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:25,900
whoever has the best performance during class.

232
00:21:26,370 --> 00:21:27,500
Just one person

233
00:21:28,270 --> 00:21:32,130
will get a chance to star in the company's next series.

234
00:21:33,170 --> 00:21:33,670
Yay!

235
00:21:33,970 --> 00:21:40,700
Okay, we have a new friend joining our class today, so

236
00:21:40,770 --> 00:21:43,170
could our new friend please introduce themself?

237
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:51,670
My name is Sun.

238
00:21:57,470 --> 00:22:00,470
Sun, have you done any previous work before?

239
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:01,730
Could you share it with us?

240
00:22:03,870 --> 00:22:04,670
No, I haven't.

241
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:09,130
Oh, it could be modeling, commercials,

242
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:11,270
or even being an influencer.

243
00:22:11,430 --> 00:22:12,230
Never.

244
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,170
That's alright if you haven't. It’s fine.

245
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:18,400
Then let's start our lesson.

246
00:22:18,830 --> 00:22:19,630
Okay?

247
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,270
So today, after we finish our relaxation,

248
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:28,000
we are going to learn about facial expressions.

249
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:31,070
Facial expressions, as we all know,

250
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:32,870
is how we express emotions on our faces.

251
00:22:32,930 --> 00:22:37,930
Facial expression is one way humans communicate.

252
00:22:41,970 --> 00:22:43,430
the eyes never lie.

253
00:22:43,470 --> 00:22:48,070
Therefore, when we act, we must feel it from inside.

254
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:13,500
That class was so boring, sitting for so long made me ache all over.

255
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:27,970
By the way, who is your manager?

256
00:23:33,170 --> 00:23:35,400
That new kid of Kajorn who just passed the audition,

257
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:36,700
who the hell is he?

258
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:50,530
Dummy: So, what is the Children's Day official motto for this year?

259
00:23:55,370 --> 00:23:56,170
You dummy.

260
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:57,570
Huh?

261
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:02,130
Do you know what this year's Children's Day official motto is?

262
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:05,070
I don't know.

263
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:08,670
I haven't been to a Children's Day event in ages. So I didn't think I'd need to know.

264
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:12,730
Why?

265
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:15,670
Hey! Wait a minute.

266
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:17,430
Is there a written exam in class or something?

267
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,000
What's the matter?

268
00:24:55,070 --> 00:24:56,370
Is your camera missing?

269
00:25:49,930 --> 00:25:52,300
Shit, who the fuck did this?

270
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:05,870
What are you doing?

271
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:12,800
I'll try to fix it.

272
00:26:14,530 --> 00:26:15,730
In case it still works.

273
00:26:17,470 --> 00:26:20,300
Please don't lose it or break it.

274
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,330
This came out of my personal wallet.

275
00:26:31,670 --> 00:26:32,900
Find a way to get rid of him.

276
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,670
I'm Two-O, nice to meet you.

277
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,270
You probably won't last a month.

278
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,330
I'm Wave.

279
00:26:55,330 --> 00:26:56,670
Most of the kids in your class

280
00:26:56,700 --> 00:26:59,370
are only joined just a little bit before you.

281
00:26:59,870 --> 00:27:01,230
There's this one guy named Ten.

282
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:02,730
That one...

283
00:27:03,670 --> 00:27:06,300
is an investor's son. They sponsor him to get roles in every project.

284
00:27:07,830 --> 00:27:09,470
Even if he acts poorly, no one dares to criticize him.

285
00:27:13,930 --> 00:27:15,000
Please turn off your communication devices.

286
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:15,970
Two seats, please.

287
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:16,300
Yes.

288
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:18,000
Please turn off your devices and refrain from taking photos.

289
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:18,500
Alright.

290
00:27:18,530 --> 00:27:19,330
Thank you.

291
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:21,570
This way, please.

292
00:27:21,570 --> 00:27:22,800
Please turn off your communication devices.

293
00:27:22,970 --> 00:27:23,770
Thank you.

294
00:27:30,830 --> 00:27:31,870
I love you.

295
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,200
You foolish.

296
00:27:34,770 --> 00:27:36,300
You can't run away from yourself.

297
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:37,330
Accept it.

298
00:27:40,770 --> 00:27:41,830
Just let me go.

299
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:45,930
Oh, why is that, my darling?

300
00:27:46,570 --> 00:27:48,470
Are you really going to give up like this?

301
00:27:49,570 --> 00:27:54,330
Serves you right for being all alone. It's all because of you.

302
00:27:54,730 --> 00:27:55,530
Stop.

303
00:28:02,100 --> 00:28:02,900
In the past,

304
00:28:05,030 --> 00:28:06,770
I kept running away from destiny.

305
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,270
Running away from good intentions.

306
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:15,630
Running away even from my own shadow.

307
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:21,900
But it followed me everywhere.

308
00:28:25,230 --> 00:28:27,000
In the end, the one who destroyed everything

309
00:28:32,870 --> 00:28:33,930
was myself.

310
00:28:40,730 --> 00:28:41,770
It's quite funny, isn't it?

311
00:28:45,930 --> 00:28:47,470
Putting myself out there to help him.

312
00:28:55,170 --> 00:28:56,000
Kissing him.

313
00:28:58,970 --> 00:29:01,130
While his hand was stabbing me repeatedly.

314
00:29:10,930 --> 00:29:13,170
But today, I didn't come back to ask for reasons.

315
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,400
I just came back to say that

316
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,130
every good intention that was once trampled on

317
00:29:34,470 --> 00:29:36,800
will become a fire that consumes me.

318
00:29:42,630 --> 00:29:43,770
And I will be the one

319
00:29:46,570 --> 00:29:48,600
who makes him burn down to ashes with me.

320
00:29:57,830 --> 00:29:58,300
What do you think?

321
00:29:59,430 --> 00:30:02,670
Sky's performance is absolutely amazing, isn't it?

322
00:30:21,930 --> 00:30:25,070
Sky’s performance is incredibly meaningful.

323
00:30:26,530 --> 00:30:27,900
Even though I don't quite understand it,

324
00:30:29,070 --> 00:30:31,730
it was a very powerful performance.

325
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,170
Powerful enough to draw something out from within me.

326
00:30:36,330 --> 00:30:38,070
After watching the play finish,

327
00:30:38,430 --> 00:30:42,900
I began to get a gist of what acting really is.

328
00:30:59,830 --> 00:31:00,970
Hello, Mr. Songbaht.

329
00:31:00,970 --> 00:31:01,870
Hello, Mr. Songbaht.

330
00:31:02,800 --> 00:31:04,900
I was informed today that you would be coming.

331
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:06,770
Please, step inside.

332
00:31:10,230 --> 00:31:11,130
Enjoy yourself.

333
00:31:11,170 --> 00:31:11,700
This way, please.

334
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:23,970
Hello, Mr. Songbaht.

335
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:30,200
You're not the person from yesterday.

336
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:31,870
Please follow me.

337
00:31:44,830 --> 00:31:46,100
Where are you taking me?

338
00:31:47,630 --> 00:31:50,100
The person who wants to see you is waiting upstairs.

339
00:31:50,930 --> 00:31:51,730
Up this way, please.

340
00:32:17,930 --> 00:32:19,470
Finally you’re here, Songbaht.

341
00:32:19,930 --> 00:32:21,900
The one who dares to hit on my Jay.

342
00:32:24,530 --> 00:32:25,730
Are you his bodyguard?

343
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,770
If there's anyone who needs a bodyguard around here,

344
00:32:35,670 --> 00:32:36,470
you're right.

345
00:32:36,930 --> 00:32:38,270
It's my Jay.

346
00:32:41,330 --> 00:32:42,570
What is this?

347
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:47,400
You look nothing special at all.

348
00:32:50,170 --> 00:32:51,830
What did you use to woo Jay in?

349
00:32:54,270 --> 00:32:56,870
I’m asking, what did you use to woo Jay?

350
00:32:58,630 --> 00:32:59,230
I used money.

351
00:33:04,970 --> 00:33:05,970
How much did you use?

352
00:33:06,830 --> 00:33:07,630
Two baht.

353
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,100
You’re funny

354
00:33:16,470 --> 00:33:17,270
Two baht.

355
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:21,700
Which isn't the amount of money, but it's you yourself?

356
00:33:22,370 --> 00:33:24,000
You're using a metaphor

357
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:27,670
that you used yourself to win him over, right?

358
00:33:28,470 --> 00:33:30,300
And you're trying to make jokes out of the situation

359
00:33:31,930 --> 00:33:34,370
just to make me laugh, is that it?

360
00:33:37,730 --> 00:33:38,730
It’s a clever move. Not gonna lie.

361
00:33:39,130 --> 00:33:39,630
Huh.

362
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:44,870
But for my Jay to actually allow someone into his office, there must be something more special.

363
00:33:45,030 --> 00:33:48,370
Because my Jay rarely shows interest in anyone.

364
00:33:49,730 --> 00:33:50,530
Well?

365
00:33:51,770 --> 00:33:52,700
Show me what you've got.

366
00:33:52,730 --> 00:33:54,270
What makes you better than everyone else?

367
00:33:58,470 --> 00:34:00,230
How dare you laugh at me?

368
00:34:02,030 --> 00:34:03,430
You don't have to act tough.

369
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,970
I know you're a nice person.

370
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:11,830
Can you really see through it all?

371
00:34:12,070 --> 00:34:13,870
That everything I did was just an act.

372
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:18,630
Well, well, well.

373
00:34:19,500 --> 00:34:25,030
Then at least you passed the grueling first stage of interviews here.

374
00:34:32,429 --> 00:34:34,570
In that case, if you want to ask anything, go ahead.

375
00:34:34,870 --> 00:34:36,500
I'll answer whatever you're curious about.

376
00:34:37,830 --> 00:34:38,770
Just one question.

377
00:34:41,570 --> 00:34:43,770
Does your Jay have any other names?

378
00:34:45,929 --> 00:34:48,330
My Jay only goes by one name, Jay.

379
00:34:48,870 --> 00:34:50,300
How could he possibly have another name?

380
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:57,900
What? What are you thinking?

381
00:34:58,470 --> 00:35:00,330
Why are you making that face?

382
00:35:02,900 --> 00:35:03,600
It’s nothing.

383
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:06,570
At least I’m certain now

384
00:35:06,870 --> 00:35:08,900
that he isn’t Director Arthur in disguise.

385
00:35:14,230 --> 00:35:17,270
Actually, my Jay doesn't really like this name that much.

386
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:19,900
But he had to go to America,

387
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,670
and didn't want a new English name.

388
00:35:22,700 --> 00:35:24,330
So he just happened to like this name.

389
00:35:25,770 --> 00:35:27,200
It's like...

390
00:35:29,100 --> 00:35:29,770
like….

391
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:31,670
because he was so young at that time.

392
00:35:33,770 --> 00:35:34,970
But my Jay,

393
00:35:35,170 --> 00:35:37,400
is both handsome and kind-hearted.

394
00:35:38,530 --> 00:35:41,000
Especially his face when he smiles

395
00:35:45,470 --> 00:35:47,000
he looks like a little angel.

396
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:50,700
Alright.

397
00:35:52,870 --> 00:35:54,830
My Jay is probably expecting you.

398
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:57,070
Go see him quickly.

399
00:35:57,770 --> 00:35:58,570
Oh!

400
00:36:01,830 --> 00:36:04,330
Don't tell Jay that we talked.

401
00:36:04,930 --> 00:36:06,570
Consider this a secret between the two of us only.

402
00:36:07,330 --> 00:36:08,970
You absolutely must not let Jay know.

403
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,830
What secret are you talking about?

404
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:19,130
Why can't I know?

405
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:22,470
A secret? There's no secret.

406
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,630
Why would I have any silly secret with you, huh?

407
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:27,700
Good to hear.

408
00:36:29,670 --> 00:36:31,500
Then I'll take this guy with me now.

409
00:36:32,730 --> 00:36:35,630
Sure, you can go together, both of you.

410
00:36:36,370 --> 00:36:37,470
Oh, hey Jay.

411
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:39,330
You really should

412
00:36:41,070 --> 00:36:44,330
stop sitting here working with a deadly look on your face until dawn.

413
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:48,200
When the staff see you working hard, they start doing the same.

414
00:36:48,570 --> 00:36:51,300
I'm getting tired of paying them overtime.

415
00:36:52,470 --> 00:36:54,230
You're causing trouble for me, you know?

416
00:36:57,270 --> 00:36:58,070
And this!

417
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,730
No one is drinking it.

418
00:37:07,070 --> 00:37:08,500
So take it back with you.

419
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:11,470
And whatever you do with it is your business.

420
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:19,900
Songbaht, If you dare to drink Jay's stuff,

421
00:37:20,670 --> 00:37:21,500
you're dead man for sure.

422
00:37:59,700 --> 00:38:01,670
What did that old man tell you?

423
00:38:03,870 --> 00:38:04,670
Nothing much.

424
00:38:06,370 --> 00:38:08,700
He just asked how I hit on you.

425
00:38:10,230 --> 00:38:11,370
And what did you say?

426
00:38:13,270 --> 00:38:14,530
That I used two baht to hit on you.

427
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:17,670
You've got a point.

428
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:19,500
And then what?

429
00:38:21,230 --> 00:38:22,230
What do you mean, then what?

430
00:38:23,030 --> 00:38:24,030
That's all there was.

431
00:38:27,370 --> 00:38:28,570
If you tell me,

432
00:38:32,630 --> 00:38:34,330
I'll cut your workload for today in half.

433
00:38:35,530 --> 00:38:36,330
What workload?

434
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,730
Watch all the movies in here.

435
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:47,400
And read that pile of scripts over there too.

436
00:38:53,930 --> 00:38:54,730
Oh.

437
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:56,700
If necessary,

438
00:39:04,470 --> 00:39:07,600
you can drink this tonic while you work.

439
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:09,700
I don't mind.

440
00:39:11,430 --> 00:39:12,730
And how long do I have to keep doing this?

441
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:26,400
Until you’re finished, of course.

442
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,500
Are you crazy?

443
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:31,100
I'm not crazy.

444
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:34,130
Because I'll bring more tomorrow.

445
00:41:01,070 --> 00:41:01,870
What are you doing?

446
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:11,830
Have you ever been fucked by a man?

447
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:18,630
Why are you asking this?

448
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:23,100
I’m just curious.

449
00:41:29,770 --> 00:41:31,000
Usually, I'm a top.

450
00:41:32,270 --> 00:41:33,070
Usually?

451
00:41:34,300 --> 00:41:35,970
So that means you have been bottom before.

452
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:48,070
It was just one time.

453
00:41:50,430 --> 00:41:51,270
And then what?

454
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:53,630
That's it, it's over.

455
00:41:55,030 --> 00:41:56,100
Who was that guy?

456
00:42:02,070 --> 00:42:05,800
Did you love him?

457
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:07,600
It was just one time.

458
00:42:08,770 --> 00:42:10,130
It probably wasn't love or anything.

459
00:42:13,470 --> 00:42:14,900
If it wasn't love,

460
00:42:16,630 --> 00:42:18,630
then that person probably wasn't important.

461
00:42:21,930 --> 00:42:24,170
So why did you sleep with him?

462
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,570
I think you should stop focusing on that.

463
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:32,830
I have work to do.

464
00:42:43,370 --> 00:42:44,500
I also

465
00:42:46,130 --> 00:42:48,070
slept with a man five years ago.

466
00:42:49,830 --> 00:42:52,000
And I'm currently looking for him.

467
00:42:53,670 --> 00:42:55,470
I hope you find him soon then.

468
00:42:58,170 --> 00:42:59,870
Aren't you even a little jealous?

469
00:43:02,930 --> 00:43:03,800
Why should I be?

470
00:43:06,330 --> 00:43:07,470
What are we to each other?

471
00:43:24,330 --> 00:43:26,400
This is it. Let's go.

472
00:43:27,200 --> 00:43:28,270
Do your best!

473
00:43:28,770 --> 00:43:30,530
Learning action choreography is so much fun.

474
00:43:31,700 --> 00:43:33,430
It fulfills my childhood dream too.

475
00:43:34,830 --> 00:43:36,570
Hmm, seeing the gym makes me feel like...

476
00:43:37,100 --> 00:43:38,730
You know, my friends used to call me

477
00:43:38,770 --> 00:43:40,200
Kajorn the jabber.

478
00:43:48,900 --> 00:43:49,700
What's wrong?

479
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:53,730
About the camera, I'm sorry, Bro.

480
00:43:54,970 --> 00:43:56,230
I'll get it fixed for you as soon as possible.

481
00:44:00,830 --> 00:44:02,300
we don't really need the camera anymore.

482
00:44:03,030 --> 00:44:03,900
Don't overthink, okay?

483
00:44:15,630 --> 00:44:16,530
Thanks, Bro.

484
00:44:18,330 --> 00:44:19,130
Go get 'em.

485
00:44:25,870 --> 00:44:27,770
Don't...don't go get yourself in trouble.

486
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:32,270
That was half of my monthly salary.

487
00:44:33,930 --> 00:44:34,970
But it's just a camera.

488
00:44:35,330 --> 00:44:36,130
Just a camera.

489
00:44:43,870 --> 00:44:45,100
Alright, everyone stand up.

490
00:44:49,870 --> 00:44:53,600
Okay, today I'll check everyone's combat skills...

491
00:44:54,100 --> 00:44:55,600
by having a sparring trial.

492
00:44:57,730 --> 00:44:58,530
It's fine.

493
00:44:59,870 --> 00:45:02,170
Remember, this is just a practice.

494
00:45:03,970 --> 00:45:04,800
Go on, pick your gloves.

495
00:45:10,730 --> 00:45:11,730
Hey, worthless shit.

496
00:45:12,170 --> 00:45:13,870
Today, I'm choosing to spar with you.

497
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:16,470
I heard that you called me a fuck face.

498
00:45:16,800 --> 00:45:20,230
You talked shit behind my back that I got roles in the series just because my dad is loaded?

499
00:45:21,330 --> 00:45:24,100
Since you're so mouthy, do you dare step up and trade blows with me on the ring, bastard?

500
00:45:27,070 --> 00:45:28,030
What's going on?

501
00:45:29,570 --> 00:45:30,600
Coach, this has nothing to do with you.

502
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:33,300
Unless you want it to, Coach.

503
00:45:33,930 --> 00:45:34,900
If you want to lose your job.

504
00:45:37,570 --> 00:45:38,670
It's fine, Coach.

505
00:45:39,900 --> 00:45:42,770
Good, you're dead meat.

506
00:45:58,870 --> 00:45:59,900
What are you trying to do?

507
00:46:02,870 --> 00:46:05,870
You know what will happen to you

508
00:46:06,170 --> 00:46:07,300
if you actually beat him up right?

509
00:46:10,830 --> 00:46:12,400
I just want to give you a heads-up.

510
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:13,800
Think carefully.

511
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:17,970
Why did Ten orchestrate this situation? What does he want?

512
00:46:19,070 --> 00:46:23,400
And if you accidentally punch him for real other people around you

513
00:46:24,030 --> 00:46:25,330
might get dragged into trouble too.

514
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:27,370
Not to mention your manager.

515
00:46:34,570 --> 00:46:37,170
Alright, start when you're ready.

516
00:46:38,370 --> 00:46:42,070
But don't forget, this is only a practice for the performance.

517
00:46:50,570 --> 00:46:52,800
Don't think this is just practice, loser.

518
00:46:53,130 --> 00:46:56,630
Because I definitely won't let a filthy rat who talks behind people's backs like you get away.

519
00:47:12,270 --> 00:47:15,430
Other people around you might get dragged into this mess too.

520
00:48:07,430 --> 00:48:08,570
Do whatever you want.

521
00:48:08,970 --> 00:48:09,870
Just make sure he can't survive here.

522
00:48:10,570 --> 00:48:11,830
Find a way to get rid of him.

523
00:48:13,530 --> 00:48:14,570
How are you doing?

524
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:19,130
Sorry about earlier.

525
00:48:19,930 --> 00:48:21,270
We couldn't help you at all.

526
00:48:22,870 --> 00:48:24,730
Even Coach Tommy couldn't stop him.

527
00:48:25,570 --> 00:48:27,130
How could we possibly help Sun?

528
00:48:35,870 --> 00:48:40,500
In that case, should we go for a drink tonight?

529
00:48:42,830 --> 00:48:43,970
Think of it as a way to unwind.

530
00:48:51,070 --> 00:48:52,100
But if you're not up for it,

531
00:48:52,430 --> 00:48:53,630
it's totally fine.

532
00:48:54,430 --> 00:48:55,670
We can do it next time.

533
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,000
Let's go.

534
00:48:58,100 --> 00:48:58,900
I can handle it.

535
00:49:02,530 --> 00:49:03,600
Where are we going?

536
00:49:18,630 --> 00:49:23,530
Right here, this place. It's very famous in our industry.

537
00:49:24,770 --> 00:49:28,730
Honestly, I was so shocked the first time I came here.

538
00:49:29,930 --> 00:49:32,500
Never mind, I'm fine.

539
00:49:33,770 --> 00:49:34,570
By the way,

540
00:49:35,270 --> 00:49:36,670
have you been here before?

541
00:49:37,630 --> 00:49:39,200
How come you don't look excited at all?

542
00:49:40,270 --> 00:49:41,370
How could I have been here?

543
00:49:41,770 --> 00:49:42,570
This place

544
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:45,170
is only reserved for A-list celebrities in the industry.

545
00:49:46,430 --> 00:49:49,130
Without an invitation, you can't even get in.

546
00:49:50,830 --> 00:49:51,630
Let's go.

547
00:50:02,170 --> 00:50:04,330
Two-O, the usual room today right?

548
00:50:05,030 --> 00:50:07,630
Awesome, the usual room is freaking huge.

549
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:10,970
Sun, I'm telling you, this room is extremely private.

550
00:50:12,030 --> 00:50:13,370
Hello, do you have a reservation?

551
00:50:13,470 --> 00:50:14,530
Yes, under Wave.

552
00:50:14,870 --> 00:50:17,070
Ah, Khun Wave. Please follow me to room V4.

553
00:50:17,170 --> 00:50:17,970
Sure.

554
00:50:19,070 --> 00:50:19,870
Sun, let's go.

555
00:50:28,670 --> 00:50:29,470
Cheers.

556
00:50:29,730 --> 00:50:30,530
Go.

557
00:50:30,770 --> 00:50:31,570
Woo!

558
00:50:38,800 --> 00:50:41,870
Actually, we are so freaking lucky.

559
00:50:42,500 --> 00:50:45,670
Because this place only welcomes top celebrities

560
00:50:46,370 --> 00:50:48,030
